Kwale Governor Salim Mvurya on Tuesday took his campaigns to his main rival and Wiper candidate Chirau Mwakwere&rsquo;s doorstep.He launched projects and warned Mwakwere against tainting his name during his campaigns.Mvurya told Mwakwere to show what he has done for residents.&ldquo;Let Mwakwere tell you what he did for you when you gave him a chance to represent you for 10 years and then compare that with what I have done for the four the years I have been in office,&rdquo; he said, addressing supporters in Baraza Park in Kwale town.Mvurya opened a drug store and administration block at Kwale Level 4 Hospital in Matuga constituency which cost Sh39.4 million.He said plans are underway to improve facilities at the hospital.&ldquo;What we have done today attests to my pragmatic leadership and I commit to do more in the health sector if reelected so that our people do not have to travel to Coast Provincial General Hospital in Mombasa,&rdquo; Mvurya said. He said Mwakwere had nothing to offer residents. &ldquo;You are eying my seat to achieve your selfish desires. We know who you really are,&rdquo; Mvurya said.